h2 class=\"din\">4. Guidelines &amp; Principles</h2>\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"innn\"><p>Users should take great pride in following these guidelines and principles as a more vibrant\r\n    social and information network will result. The guidelines and principles have been developed to promote:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li> The integrity of the community</li>\r\n      <li> The quality of the information collected and made available</li>\r\n      <li> The quality of the communication</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>The guidelines and principles provide the framework for creating information and interacting with Heard Mentality\r\n      as it is different than the other social networks. We also request the help of our community to enforce these\r\n      policies by flagging those interactions you feel violate the guidelines and principles or by volunteering to be a\r\n      moderator [How you can help]. Badges [link to badges] will be awarded to those users who abide by and assist in\r\n      enforcing the guidelines and principles.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"table-bor-form clearfix\">\r\n      <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1\">\r\n        <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1-title\"><h6>In all user interaction:</h6></div>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Concise</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Clean</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Original</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Golden Rule</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1\">\r\n        <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1-title\"><h6>Issues:</h6></div>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Concise</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Clean</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Original</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Golden Rule</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1 border-none-last\">\r\n        <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1-title\"><h6>Posts:</h6></div>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Concise</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Clean</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Original</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Golden Rule</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <h6>Principles:</h6>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Concise:</span> Take pity on the reader – information should be presented in a non\r\n      verbose manner. Pride should be taken from wording things concisely. This will ensure users can consume and retain\r\n      a larger amount of information as well as making technical features like the translations and search more\r\n      effective. Studies also show that more people will stop to read a shorter comment and more likely to pass over\r\n      longer ones.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Clean:</span> No profanity please. Consider all users when choosing your language.\r\n      People take the posting more seriously when it refrains from using harsh and negative words. Also, abbreviations\r\n      should be avoided as other users or the translation feature may not understand.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Original:</span> Pleased do not repeat anything that has been already posted. Any\r\n      duplicate content dilutes the overall accuracy of the compiled information. Any new issue or posting added to\r\n      Heard Mentality should be significantly different than existing content. Good practice would be to “agree” with\r\n      the posting you may want to reiterate or voting on the issue that already exists - this will ultimately draw more\r\n      attention to it.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Golden Rule:</span> This is the fundamental rule to make any social community work.\r\n      Please treat others like you would like to be treated yourself and you in return will get the same.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Important:</span> Issues should be classifiable into the provided high level sections.\r\n      Please do not post issues that could be considered unimportant, for example: The hairdo of a certain celebrity or\r\n      which restaurant or movie is best. While these may be important questions, these are not the types of issues to be\r\n      discussed here.\r\n\r\n    <p></p><span class=\"highlighted\">Unbiased:</span> Issues should be posted in an unbiased and non-leading way. Issues\r\n    should be posed simply and direct. All realistic possible answers should be introduced.</p><p><span\r\n      class=\"highlighted\">On Point:</span> When creating or replying to a debate, please discuss only the issue at hand\r\n      and reframe from any outside discussions. The Heard Mentality debate works differently than others web forums. We\r\n      ask you to post meaningful insight or references on the issue and refrain from exchanging pleasantries (this can\r\n      be done through other communication channels). Recognition of one’s point well made or a good reply to one’s post\r\n      is encouraged by \"agreeing\".</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Truthful:</span> Never post any false information. Strive to post only what can be\r\n      backed up by facts. References and links should always be provided when available.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Considerate:</span> Discussions within the debate are about issues and questions\r\n      surrounding those issues. Postings should never be directed to other users directly, nor should they treat any\r\n      other user disrespectfully. Please keep personal emotion out of discussion and consider each person’s right to\r\n      their own view.</p></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','<div id=\"about_us_page_content\">\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"din\">1.About</h2>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"what_is_hm\"><h3 class=\"din\">1.1 What Heard Mentality is about</h3>\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"innn\"><p>Heard Mentality is an open and unbiased forum for global opinion for history’s and today’s most\r\n    debated issues.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Heard Mentality sees the internet and the limitless possibilities it presents as the most powerful tool for\r\n      strengthening the globally important societal virtues of liberty, equality and freedom. People from around the\r\n      world can now share ideas and experiences like never before in history – creating opportunities never thought\r\n      before possible.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Heard Mentality strives to fill the role in this new world of interconnectedness and communication as the\r\n      impartial meeting place on the internet where information and public opinion on important issues can be shared in\r\n      an open and structured forum.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>We recognize that real value is generated by the integrity of our user community and the site – developing\r\n      policies and mechanisms that promote the creation of user driven knowledge and opinion base while still protecting\r\n      the individual users’ rights to privacy [link to privacy policy].</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>All site enhancements and policy development and enforcement will be guided by Heard Mentality’s principle of\r\n      ‘always do good’. The user never need fear that any other motive than altruism exists. New site features will be\r\n      launched to facilitate the creation, compilation and the sharing of global free information - in hopes of creating\r\n      new understandings and wisdom.</p></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"organization\"><h3 class=\"din\">1.2 Organization</h3>\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"innn\"><p>The Heard Mentality website is operated by The Heard Mentality Foundation - a non-profit\r\n    foundation with a mission of providing a free, open and unbiased gauge of global public opinion.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Heard Mentality provides the network to support productive and constructive debate and truthful information\r\n      sharing on global issues.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>Heard Mentality has no ownership - simply a dedicated team working together to m