li> The integrity of the community</li>\r\n      <li> The quality of the information collected and made available</li>\r\n      <li> The quality of the communication</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>The guidelines and principles provide the framework for creating information and interacting with Heard Mentality\r\n      as it is different than the other social networks. We also request the help of our community to enforce these\r\n      policies by flagging those interactions you feel violate the guidelines and principles or by volunteering to be a\r\n      moderator [How you can help]. Badges [link to badges] will be awarded to those users who abide by and assist in\r\n      enforcing the guidelines and principles.</p>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"table-bor-form clearfix\">\r\n      <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1\">\r\n        <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1-title\"><h6>In all user interaction:</h6></div>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Concise</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Clean</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Original</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Golden Rule</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1\">\r\n        <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1-title\"><h6>Issues:</h6></div>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Concise</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Clean</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Original</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Golden Rule</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1 border-none-last\">\r\n        <div class=\"table-bor-form-item-1-title\"><h6>Posts:</h6></div>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Concise</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Clean</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Original</a></li>\r\n          <li><a href=\"#\">Golden Rule</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <h6>Principles:</h6>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Concise:</span> Take pity on the reader – information should be presented in a non\r\n      verbose manner. Pride should be taken from wording things concisely. This will ensure users can consume and retain\r\n      a larger amount of information as well as making technical features like the translations and search more\r\n      effective. Studies also show that more people will stop to read a shorter comment and more likely to pass over\r\n      longer ones.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Clean:</span> No profanity please. Consider all users when choosing your language.\r\n      People take the posting more seriously when it refrains from using harsh and negative words. Also, abbreviations\r\n      should be avoided as other users or the translation feature may not understand.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Original:</span> Pleased do not repeat anything that has been already posted. Any\r\n      duplicate content dilutes the overall accuracy of the compiled information. Any new issue or posting added to\r\n      Heard Mentality should be significantly different than existing content. Good practice would be to “agree” with\r\n      the posting you may want to reiterate or voting on the issue that already exists - this will ultimately draw more\r\n      attention to it.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Golden Rule:</span> This is the fundamental rule to make any social community work.\r\n      Please treat others like you would like to be treated yourself and you in return will get the same.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Important:</span> Issues should be classifiable into the provided high level sections.\r\n      Please do not post issues that could be considered unimportant, for example: The hairdo of a certain celebrity or\r\n      which restaurant or movie is best. While these may be important questions, these are not the types of issues to be\r\n      discussed here.\r\n\r\n    <p></p><span class=\"highlighted\">Unbiased:</span> Issues should be posted in an unbiased and non-leading way. Issues\r\n    should be posed simply and direct. All realistic possible answers should be introduced.</p><p><span\r\n      class=\"highlighted\">On Point:</span> When creating or replying to a debate, please discuss only the issue at hand\r\n      and reframe from any outside discussions. The Heard Mentality debate works differently than others web forums. We\r\n      ask you to post meaningful insight or references on the issue and refrain from exchanging pleasantries (this can\r\n      be done through other communication channels). Recognition of one’s point well made or a good reply to one’s post\r\n      is encouraged by \"agreeing\".</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Truthful:</span> Never post any false information. Strive to post only what can be\r\n      backed up by facts. References and links should always be provided when available.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p><span class=\"highlighted\">Considerate:</span> Discussions within the debate are about issues and questions\r\n      surrounding those issues. Postings should never be directed to other users directly, nor should they treat any\r\n      other user disrespectfully. Please keep personal emotion out of discussion and consider each person’s right to\r\n      their own view.</p></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','',1358604171,3),(53,53,1,'Privacy Policy','<p id=\"internal-source-marker_0.5534311117187353\" dir=\"ltr\"><span>Heard  Mentality strives to fill the role in this new world of  interconnectedness and communication as the impartial meeting place on  the internet where information and public opinion on important issues  can be shared in an open and structured forum. HM recognizes that real  value is generated by the integrity of our user community and the site –  developing policies and mechanisms that promote the creation of user  driven knowledge and opinion base while still protecting the individual  users’ rights to privacy.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><a name=\"privacy\"></a><h1 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Privacy Policy</span></h1><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Heard  Mentality Privacy Policy describes the rules for the collection, use,  and disclosure of your personal information provided while accessing,  using, and contributing with Heard Mentality (hereinafter “HM”).</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM Privacy Policy adheres to the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act of Canada.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>By  logging in and using the HM website and providing al the information  required to do so, you are expressly and voluntarily accepting the terms  and conditions of HM Privacy Policy and HM Terms of Use and HM  Guidelines.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>You  have the right to withdraw your consent to HM collection and processing  of your Personal Information at any time by closing your account, but  keep in mind that your withdrawal of consent will not be retroactive.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>If you have questions about HM Privacy Policy, please do not hesitate to contact us at:</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Privacy@heardmentality.org</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span><br /><span>&nbsp;</span></p><a name=\"personal\"></a><h1 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Personal Information</span></h1><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>In  order to access, use, and contribute with the HM website, You need to  either log in using one your current social networks or email account or  by creating a HM account. Some of this information is your name,  country, IP address, alternate contact information, and password as well  as your religious or political beliefs and personal views or opinions  resulting from the use of the HM website (hereinafter “Personal  Information”) </span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The  HM website may send one or more cookies - a message, or segment of  data, containing information and details about You and your preferences  in the HM website which identify You when revisiting the HM website. The  HM website uses cookies to improve the quality of the HM Services (as  defined in the HM Terms of Use), including for storing your preferences,  improving search results, and tracking your trends, such as how you  navigate the site.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span><br /><span>&nbsp;</span></p><a name=\"uses\"></a><h1 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Uses of Personal Information</span></h1><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The  HM website may store and maintain your Personal Information to keep the  HM Services, use, and the HM Purpose ((as defined in the HM Terms of  Use).</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The  HM website may process your Personal Information. By using and  contributing with the HM website, You are providing certain Personal  Information that may identify You individually and even reveal your  religious or political beliefs and personal views or opinions about the  issues discussed in the HM website. HM may process said information in  order to fulfill the HM Purpose as an impartial meeting place on the  internet where information and public opinion on important issues can be  shared in an open and structured forum. As part of the HM Purpose, this  Personal Information may be processed so as to provide statistics about  HM’s users’ positions with respect to the issues discussed in the HM  website.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM  may disclose analysis and statistics resulting from your Personal  Information resulting from your use of the HM website to the appropriate  recipients only in accordance with HM Purpose. This excludes your name,  alternate contact information, and password, particularly because the  disclosure of those is not in accordance with the HM Purpose.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM may also use your Personal Information to develop new features in accordance with the HM Purpose.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The  HM website will not collect or use your Personal Information for  purposes other than those described in HM Privacy Policy, HM Terms of  Use and HM Guidelines unless You have granted HM your prior consent.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span><br /><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Updating your Personal Information</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Through  your regular use of the HM website, You may correct or update data if  it is inaccurate or delete such data, unless it is not otherwise  required to be retained by law or for legitimate HM Purpose.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><a name=\"third-parties\"></a><h1 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Third Parties</span></h1><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM does not sell, rent, or otherwise provide your Personal Information to any third parties.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM  does not share any information You have not chosen to display, unless  compelled by law, or as necessary to enforce HM Terms of Use.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM  Privacy Policy applies to HM only. HM does not control over any of the  other sites you use to log in or mentioned by any reason in the HM  website.</span></p><p><br /><br /></p><a name=\"security\"></a><h1 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Security</span></h1><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM  takes security measures to protect the HM website against unauthorized  access to or unauthorized alteration, or destruction of data. These  include internal reviews of our data collection, storage and processing  practices and security measures. However, You are responsible for  maintaining the secrecy of your unique passwords and account  information, and for controlling access to your account at all times.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>HM  restricts access to Personal Information to HM community members who  need to know