><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Heard  Mentality (hereinafter “HM”) reserves the right to change, modify, add  or remove parts of these Terms of Use at its own discretion at any time.  If major changes are made to these Terms of Use, HM will attempt to  notify You; however please be aware that You must periodically review  the most up-to-date version posted in the Heard Mentality website. Any  modification shall be effective immediately upon posting in the Heard  Mentality website unless otherwise provided. By continuing logging in or  using the Heard Mentality website You agree to any such modification. </span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>By  logging in using the Heard Mentality website You warrant HM that your  use of and content obtained from the Heard Mentality website will be in  accordance with these Terms of Use. Should you violate in any way these  Terms of Use, HM shall automatically terminate your permission herein  granted to You. &nbsp;</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>You  assume and warrant that You are of legal age in accordance with the  legislation of your country to create contractual and financial  obligations and to assume any liability in which You may incur by your  use of HM.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span><br /><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><a name=\"services\"></a><h1>Services</h1></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Heard  Mentality strives to fill the role in this new world of  interconnectedness and communication as the impartial meeting place on  the internet where information and public opinion on important issues  can be shared in an open and structured forum (hereinafter “HM  Purpose”). As such, HM intends to provide the mechanisms and tools that  promote the creation of user driven knowledge and opinion base  (hereinafter “HM Services”). HM reserves the right to update, improve or  discontinue any of the HM Services at any time.</span></p><p><s